                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.154/79: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Price</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-25T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Your 115, June 21, 2 p.m.<note n="11" xml:id="d553fn11">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Inform appropriate officials that Department expects that provisions of Law 30 of
                    1918 will be maintained and that the Panaman Government will abstain from action
                    tending to impair American Fiscal Agent’s contract.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
